-- Microsoft's Xbox Tops June U.S. Retail Home Console Sales
-- B y   C l i f f   E d w a r d s
-- 2013-07-18T22:15:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-18/microsoft-s-xbox-tops-june-u-s-retail-home-console-sales.html
Microsoft Corp. (MSFT)  said U.S. retailers
sold 140,000 Xbox 360 units in June, helping it retain the top-selling spot for game consoles for the 30th straight month.  June spending on all Xbox products, including the console,
Kinect motion-sensing peripheral and software, totaled $197
million, Redmond, Washington-based Microsoft said today in an e-mail, citing NPD Group Inc. data.  Sales of the console fell 46 percent compared with a year
earlier, when it sold 257,000 consoles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cliff Edwards in  San Francisco  at 
